  "description": "Submerged topology: Square strands in a Figure-Eight knot at maximum braid depth, filtered through a Band Pass at 280 Hz with high resonance. The alternating over/under crossing pattern of the Figure-Eight creates asymmetric spectral beating — not the smooth phase drift of detuning but a lurching, uneven rhythm from the coupling matrix's alternating signs (+0.6, -0.4). LFO1 at 0.02 Hz on filter cutoff shifts the resonant peak glacially. The Hadal zone: topology under extreme pressure.",
